• Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. POLOKWANE - Limpopo businessman Rameez Patel appeared in the Polokwane magistrate's court for his mother's murder.  Patel made a brief appearance before the case was postponed until 11 October for a bail application. READ: Rameez Patel back in court on separate murder charge The elderly woman was shot dead by an unknown gunman at her home last month. Limpopo police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the motive behind the killing was not yet known and nothing was taken from the house. The businessman is already on trial for the murder of his 28-year-old wife Fatima, who was beaten, strangled and shot in the couple's home. Patel has denied killing his wife in 2015. He has blamed an intruder for the murder. - Additional reporting ANA eNCA